The paper discusses a framework for structured query retrieval in text corpora and standardized testing corpora, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the integration of traditional procedures in natural language processing (NLP), which suggests the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of quantum-based methods and the identification of quantum structures in cognition indicate the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of the proposed framework over traditional approaches, which could be related to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
